        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I think the problem boils down to whether we should require `nvim_buf_is_valid()` as a precondition of `M.show()`. In #25628, I had similar problem regarding `nvim_buf_is_loaded()`. I chose not to require it, because otherwise I would have had to add the checks before all the invocations of `M.show()`, which I thought was a bit messy. \r\n\r\nI you agree on my view, I think the issue you're experiencing can be fixed by requiring `nvim_buf_is_valid()` as the precondition of `schedule_display()`. ",
