            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": ">I think the problem boils down to whether we should require nvim_buf_is_valid() as a precondition of M.show()\r\n\r\nI think this is reasonable. The diagnostic cache is the underlying data model that stores the state of all diagnostics, including diagnostics not associated with a valid buffer. `vim.diagnostic.show()` is the \"UI layer\", so to speak. The \"data model\" doesn't care about valid buffers, it stores any diagnostics it is given, but the \"UI layer\" _does_ care about valid buffers.",
            "created_at": "2023-12-31T18:53:53Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/26823#issuecomment-1873016567",
